721872f-a.title: Manhattan: Nassau Street - Liberty Street
721872f-a.text:
Nassau Street, north from Liberty Street and across Maiden
Lane. On the right is the fenced site upon which is to rise the
new Federal Reserve Bank. The Prescott Building is at the S. W.
corner of John Street and across from the Crockcroft Building at
the N. W. corner. The Fulton Building is at the S. W. corner of
Fulton Street.
September 15, 1921

721873f-a.title: Manhattan: Nassau Street - Liberty Street
721873f-a.text:
Nassau Street, east side, from Liberty Street, to Maiden Lane,
showing the Federal Reserve Bank building under construction. The
photographer is viewing southwestward from a point on Maiden Lane
near William Street. Nassau Street is in the right background
containing the 31 story Liberty Tower. On the left is the massive
N. Y. Mutual Life lInsurance Company building on Liberty Street.
September 15, 1921
